 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: Ambient Reconciliation — every command produces a :recon/trace datom as side-effect, enabling spec-neighborhood concentration detection through the existing guidance pipeline (INV-STORE-014, INV-GUIDANCE-021, INV-BILATERAL-002). BACKGROUND: Reconciliation failure (TSV/CTP tasks created without surfacing ACP overlap) has root cause: reconciliation only runs when agent explicitly calls braid observe. The agent bypassed reconciliation by going straight to task creation. The fix: reconciliation is a FIELD the agent exists in, not a GATE it passes through. Every command loads the store and produces JSON — adding a trace means extracting spec refs from the JSON, running 2-hop spec-graph BFS via VAET index, and writing a :recon/trace datom. Traces accumulate; after 3+ in the same spec neighborhood, the guidance system surfaces the concentration as a methodology gap. APPROACH: 5 tasks: crystallize phantom specs, schema + trace producer, graph traversal engine, concentration detector, verification. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Every command that produces output also writes :recon/trace. (B) braid task create with INV-INTERFACE-001 ref surfaces ACP tasks in trace. (C) After 5 commands in same neighborhood, braid status shows concentration warning. (D) Zero performance regression (trace adds <1ms per command). TRACES TO: INV-STORE-014, INV-GUIDANCE-021, INV-BILATERAL-002, INV-GUIDANCE-001."
